Husband and wife musicians, Violeta Osorhean, associate concert master, and Sorin Osorhean, principal French horn player, with the KZN Philharmonic Orchestra, get romantic ahead of Valentine’s Day. The duo are rehearsing for the first concert of the orchestral season of the year taking place on Thursday, 22 February. Israeli-American, Daniel Boico conducts and acclaimed young Ukraine-born pianist, Anna Dmytrenko,is the soloist. The season takes place every Thursday at the Playhouse until 15 March. Durban North News wish our readers a Valentine’s Day filled with love and happiness.